#############################
### - MadGraph commands - ###
#############################

# - Start tutorial
tutorial

# - Display more info about a command
help <command>

# - Generate process
generate p p > t t~

# - Display processes
display processes

# - If you want to know more about particles and multiparticles present, write
# - Note: This displays the particles of the model, NOT the particles of the process
display particles
display multiparticles

# - Defined interactions of the model
display interactions

# - Import a model
import model mssm
import model 2HDM
import model 2HDM_NLO

# - Customize a model
customize_model

# - Define a multiparticle label
define v = w+ w- z a

# - See multiparticle labels
display multiparticles

# - Save command history
history <filename>

# - Load a command history and execute
import command <filename>

# - Running shell commands
!ls -l

# - At this stage you can export your processes to different formats. In
# - this tutorial, we will explain how to create output for MadEvent.
# - This is done simply by typing:
output MY_FIRST_MG5_RUN

# - At any time, you can access more commands/options for running the output by
# - switching to an interactive interface for a given output folder 'MyFolder'.
# - You can do so by typing:
launch -i MyFolder

